pageContext.description: Parts of well-defined e. bev. surviving; some rippling of socket may be original; cg. fl. not fully removed - evid. all down s. sides; lump at base of one bl. wing poss. cg. flaw; fine ridge near s.m. - cg. flaw; one peg-hole open, other filled with hard material - corrosion? slight creases in s. profile at bl. wings.
pageContext.patina: Dark brown patina; patches pocked/flaked to lighter brown.
pageContext.surface: Little lumpy sur. - corr? Most of bl. e. with minor dam. prob. in ant.; large crack from s. m. 0 ant.?; some scoring of sur. may be rel. recent. Orange stained material adhering.
pageContext.collection: Oakham Museum, O.S. 693,Formerly in the collection of V.B. Gowther-Beynon
